# PipeWatch

Open-core GitHub Actions dashboard вЂ” aggregates workflow runs across multiple repositories into a single real-time interface. **PipeWatch CE** (self-hosted, Docker Compose) and **PipeWatch Cloud** (managed, `cloud.pipewatch.app`) ship from one codebase.

## Tech stack (PRD В§4.6, В§17)

- **Single repo:** pnpm workspace monorepo with **Turborepo** (`mdg-labs/pipewatch`)
- **Language:** **TypeScript** (strict, no `any`) everywhere
- **Backend API:** **Hono** + `@hono/zod-openapi` вЂ” API + webhook receiver on Fly.io
- **Worker:** **BullMQ** consumer on Fly.io Machines
- **Web client:** **Next.js** (App Router) via **OpenNext** on Cloudflare Workers
- **Marketing:** **Next.js** via OpenNext on Cloudflare Workers (separate project)
- **Persistence:** **Drizzle ORM** + **Drizzle Kit**; **Neon PostgreSQL** (hosted staging/prod); embedded Postgres in CE Docker Compose
- **Queue/cache:** **Redis** on Fly.io (hosted); Redis in CE Compose
- **Contracts/validation:** **Zod** in `packages/types`
- **Tests:** **Vitest** (unit/integration) + **Playwright** (e2e); ReportPortal reporters
- **Packages:** `apps/api` В· `apps/worker` В· `apps/web` В· `apps/marketing` В· `packages/db` В· `packages/types` В· `packages/config` В· `packages/utils`
- **Auth:** Custom **JWT** (15min) + DB-backed **refresh tokens** (httpOnly cookie, 30d) + workspace-scoped **API keys** (`pw_` prefix) вЂ” PRD В§7.1, Decision #22
- **Billing:** Stripe (cloud only); CE has no billing вЂ” PRD В§24
- **Secrets:** **Phase Cloud** (EU/Frankfurt); Phase в†’ GitHub Actions environments only; deploy workflows push to Fly/CF вЂ” PRD В§10, Decision #32/#33
- **Edition:** `PIPEWATCH_EDITION=ce|cloud` drives all feature flags via `packages/config/edition.ts` вЂ” Decision #28

### Hosted infrastructure (PRD В§4.2вЂ“В§4.3)

| Layer | Platform | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| API + webhooks | **Fly.io** | `pipewatch-{staging\|prod}-api` |
| Worker | **Fly.io** | `pipewatch-{staging\|prod}-worker` |
| Redis | **Fly.io** | `pipewatch-{staging\|prod}-redis` |
| Database | **Neon PostgreSQL** | Separate projects per env (Decision #17) |
| Dashboard | **Cloudflare Workers** | `pipewatch-{staging\|prod}-web` |
| Marketing | **Cloudflare Workers** | `pipewatch-{staging\|prod}-marketing` |

**Domains:** `pipewatch.app` (marketing) В· `cloud.pipewatch.app` (app) В· `api.pipewatch.app` (API). Staging uses `staging-*` prefixes.

CE: **Docker Compose** вЂ” single command setup, auto-migrate at API startup (Decision #36).

### CI/CD (PRD В§22, Decision #34вЂ“#35)

Reusable workflows under `.github/workflows/`. **GitHub-hosted runners** (`ubuntu-latest`). Branches: `staging` (integration + deploy) and `main` (release line).
Secrets from GitHub Actions environments (`staging`, `production`, `ci`) вЂ” synced from Phase Console, never fetched at runtime from Phase.

## Repository state

This repo is a **pnpm workspace monorepo** with **Turborepo** (`mdg-labs/pipewatch`).

**Customer documentation** lives in the sibling repo [`mdg-labs/pipewatch-docs`](https://github.com/mdg-labs/pipewatch-docs), published at [docs.pipewatch.app](https://docs.pipewatch.app) via Documentation.AI. **Engineering specs** stay in `docs/internal/` in this monorepo.

## Spec doc precedence (when docs conflict)

1. `docs/internal/PipeWatch_MVP_PRD.md` вЂ” **product source of truth**: architecture, data model, API, billing, security, edition split, resolved decisions
2. `docs/internal/PipeWatch_Page_Inventory.md` вЂ” **UI/page source of truth**: screens, layout, navigation, empty/loading/error states, edition differences

## Hard rules

- If behaviour is not defined in a spec doc, **ask before guessing**.
- Never invent fields, endpoints, flows, or plans not present in the PRD.
- **"Workspace"** is the only tenant term вЂ” not "organization" or "tenant" in code/schema.
- **Vendor-neutral schema** вЂ” `integrations`, `pipeline_runs`, `pipeline_jobs`, `pipeline_steps`, `external_*` IDs; MVP provider is `github` only (Decision #37). GitHub-specific names stay at the integration boundary.
- UI may say "workflow" for GitHub Actions; API types use `PipelineRun` / `PipelineJob`.
- **Edition differences** use `flags` from `packages/config/edition.ts` вЂ” never ad-hoc `process.env.PIPEWATCH_EDITION` checks scattered in app code.
- **No raw log storage** in MVP вЂ” link to GitHub for logs (Decision #6).
- **Webhook signature validation** is always enforced вЂ” no bypass (Decision #4).
- Single repo, no submodules, pnpm throughout вЂ” no npm or yarn lockfiles.
- CE and Cloud are the **same code path** вЂ” edition flags, not duplicate implementations.
